I've done the work with
meditation and mindfulness.

00:02:08.990 --> 00:02:11.140
And I've helped a lot
of people along the way.

00:02:11.140 --> 00:02:12.681
And I've learned a
tremendous amount.

00:02:12.681 --> 00:02:14.360
And I'm still
continuing to learn.

00:02:14.360 --> 00:02:18.280
There's no into your learning
with meditation or mindfulness.

00:02:18.280 --> 00:02:21.690
So it's just based on my
experience and my practice

00:02:21.690 --> 00:02:23.600
and with helping out others.

00:02:23.600 --> 00:02:25.970
So it's evolving process.

00:02:25.970 --> 00:02:28.680
Meditation practice,
mindless-- it's a journey.

00:02:28.680 --> 00:02:29.855
There's no end to it.

00:02:29.855 --> 00:02:32.230
We have these ideas, I think,
that we'll reach happiness,

00:02:32.230 --> 00:02:35.390
or we'll reach a point and it'll
all be good or will be done.

00:02:35.390 --> 00:02:37.710
But what I've found,
in my experience,

00:02:37.710 --> 00:02:38.845
is that it just continues.

00:02:38.845 --> 00:02:40.190
It just deepens.

00:02:40.190 --> 00:02:42.720
And that's very exciting
to me-- that there's

00:02:42.720 --> 00:02:44.790
no endpoint to any of it.

00:02:44.790 --> 00:02:47.800
You can just continue to
grow and evolve and learn.

00:02:47.800 --> 00:02:50.060
And with peace or
whatever you find

00:02:50.060 --> 00:02:53.230
for meditation, that could
just deepen over time.

